festival.introText:
The Woodland Dance Project returns for their smaller dance of the year - this one is only one day and tickets are LIMITED!

 

Following a bumper inaugural 8 parties over four years that saw old-out events, great performances from international DJs alongside local stars, and crazy scenes across 4 stages, The Woodland Dance Project is back for 2023 with a bang!

 

Set in the lush and picturesque surroundings at Vogrie Country Park, just 30 minutes from central Edinburgh,

Expect a hedonistic atmosphere of colour, magic and dance in a vibrant, natural and playful setting - The event is the first and only one of it’s kind on the East Coast.

faqs.question: When is Woodland Dance Project - Spring 2023?
faqs.answer: Woodland Dance Project - Spring takes place Saturday 13th May 2023.

faqs.question: How to get to Woodland Dance Project
Does Woodland Dance Project have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Woodland Dance Project is a non camping festival so camping equipment is not needed.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where is Woodland Dance Project?
faqs.answer: Woodlands is set in the picturesque Vogrie Country Park in Gorebridge 105 hectares of woods and Victorian parkland situated just outside Edinburgh. Exact routing information will be sent with your ticket, please follow it carefully!

faqs.question: How much is parking?
faqs.answer: Parking is £2.00 per day. No over-night camping or parking.

faqs.question: Ticket Info
faqs.answer:
• - All tickets are strictly non transferable and non refundable.
  • - Subject to Licence
  • - Management reserve the right to refuse entry regardless if you have a ticket
  • - Please note valid I.D is required on entry
  • - No dickheads

faqs.question: Can I bring food & drink into Woodland Dance Project?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Woodland Dance Project.

faqs.question: Does Woodland Dance Project have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Woodland Dance Project. There will be a strict I.D. & search policy upon entry.

reviewsDisplayFour.title: Review of Woodland Dance Project 2021
reviewsDisplayFour.body: probably one of the nicest festivals I've been to in ages. has a very small and cosy atmosphere which made things very relaxing. there was a good range of music from different styles and bpm, so you could move easily depending on your mood/energy levels. (only thing I can say to improve; it might have been nice to hear more proper old old drum and bass, or maybe some funk and soul?). generally had a really lovely time though
